<item>
            <title>[MAHOUT-837] Make build-asf-email.sh HDFS aware</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-837</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-798&quot; title=&quot;Add Examples for the ASF Mail Archive&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-798&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-798&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, build-asf-email.sh was added and it checks to see if certains tasks are already done in order to skip costly calculations.  The problem is, the checking is not HDFS aware, so in a Hadoop cluster, it repeats some unnecessary tasks (such as conversion to vectors)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
